NameChangeDaily here with the beginnings of a new story. I've been working on this "secret" project for several months now, finishing the first draft in August but hitting big delays after restructuring a fair bit of the plot. I was hoping to be finished with this by the holiday season, but it doesn't look like things will turn out that way, although it's too early to tell. I really put my heart and soul into making this as good as I can.

If I can't finish it before the end of the year, I want to at least get this first part out there. This covers the first 4 chapters, about 15500 words. Without further ado:

By NameChangeDaily
>Deer to My Heart
https://archiveofourown.org/works/35634802/chapters/88846174

A human man goes on a hunting trip, only to have it interrupted by a visit by his estranged lover, a whitetail doe anthro. Tensions run high as a blizzard leaves the pair trapped in his house for the weekend. As they reconnect, however, they confront the demons that doomed their relationship, help each other heal, and regain the faith and hope that their love is something worth fighting for.

Special thanks to Power_of_Alchemy and Happy_Dragon for beta reading my work. I believe it's much better off thanks to both of your help. Also thanks to the legend who posted this.

It will be out on SoFurry soon, should you prefer to read there.

Finished reading it right now, not bad at all but it could use some extra spice and help to really shine and polish it. The girl speaks in a very synthetic way a lot of times and it kind of ruins the feel of country doe that's one foot into society and one foot into tribalism gig you want to portray, it lacks the emotion she should really have since your main protagonist is meant or at least shown to be an emotional wall for her. You need some dynamic here, she doesn't speak much different from him tonaly and he's mostly deadpan unless its his internal dialogue where his background seems to be of a sailor. Also, narratively we start off a bit blind and I understand that is half the point but it feels as if the reveal doesn't have as much impact as it should and that the path to it should be a bit more foreshadowed. Maybe the protag parks his car and takes a long, calming breath before he picks up his milk bottles or something alongside those lines, but it feels like there isn't any real clue that things are going to be awkward or the real cause of it before they do-

Structurally, a lot of your dialogue seems to be a bit strange at times. You slap on the *he says* and so a few times but it ends up being abandoned quite a bit to just back and forth without much flavour or middle action. Spice it a little, have a rubbed shoulder, a bit lip, a sigh or a grunt as they confess to one another, as they brace to have the talks they don't want to have but need to. Mechanically it works, but it could be much better as a whole and in your delivery with just some mild effort, so best of luck in applying it. Oh also, five senses, you can probably find a few moments to sprinkle them in, they always help.

Mind you I'm being critical, but it's still an enjoyable piece. I just feel like it really needs the second draft treatment to pretty it up to its best potential.
